article.headline: Ohio 78, W. Michigan 73 (OT)
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- Bubba Walther sank two 3-point shots in overtime to help Ohio beat Western Michigan 78-73 on Tuesday night. Walther led the Bobcats (16-7, 7-3 Mid-American), with 20 points, 10 in overtime. He also made two free throws with 8.7 seconds remaining to close the scoring. David Kool led Western Michigan with 20 points. His 3-pointer with 13.4 seconds remaining trimmed the deficit to 76-73. But after Ohio's Jerome Tillman missed the front end of a one-and-one at the line, Walther stole the ball back and was fouled. Kool had a chance to win the game for the Broncos (10-13, 5-5) at the end of regulation but missed a jump shot at the top of the lane at the buzzer. Tillman and Leon Williams scored 15 points apiece for Ohio, which played its third overtime game in conference play, having lost at Miami and at Kent State. Williams also made eight rebounds, and Sonny Troutman added 12 points for the Bobcats. Western Michigan also got 12 points from Derek Drews, 11 from Joe Reitz and 10 from Shawntes Gary.
